<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911002-0152</DOCNO><DOCID>911002-0152.</DOCID><HL>   Marketing andamp; Media:   Infinity Broadcasting Corp.</HL><DATE>10/02/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   INFTA</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)</IN><NS>FINANCING AGREEMENTS (FNC)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- Infinity Broadcasting Corp. said it reached anamended credit accord with its bank group that will provideabout $50 million of additional borrowings for a revolvingcredit line.   The credit line will be used for general purposes, as wellas to reduce high-yield debt, Infinity said. The bankagreement allows the company to buy back the debt at pricesnot more than 65% of face amount. The company said that, as aresult, it will reduce debt about $50 million.</LP><TEXT>   Infinity added that its shareholders contributed about $30million of additional equity to the company under the bankagreement.</TEXT></DOC>